The paper deals with visual facial attributes and deep learning, which are both commonly associated with computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the subjective nature of facial attribute assignment, which is related to human-computer interaction (cs.HC). Additionally, the use of neural networks for predictive modeling is a common topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the use of image databases and crowd ratings suggests a connection to multimedia (cs.MM).
